- **Latest Version**: @auth0/nextjs-auth0 v4.22.0
- **Key Config Options**:
  - `domain`: Your Auth0 domain.
  - `clientId`: Your Auth0 client ID.
  - `clientSecret`: Your Auth0 client secret.
  - `audience`: The API audience for your application.
- **CLI Commands**:
  - To install the SDK: `npm install @auth0/nextjs-auth0`
  - To initialize the SDK in your Next.js project, follow the steps in the [QuickStart guide](https://github.com/auth0/nextjs-auth0#quickstart).
- **Example Configuration**:
  ```javascript
  // next.config.mjs
  import { withAuth0 } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0';

  const config = {
    auth0: {
      domain: 'your-auth0-domain.auth0.com',
      clientId: 'your-client-id',
      clientSecret: 'your-client-secret',
      audience: 'https://your-api-audience'
    }
  };

  export default withAuth0(config);
  ```
- **Example Usage**:
  ```javascript
  // pages/api/protected.js
  import { getSession } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0';

  export default async function handler(req, res) {
    const session = await getSession(req, res);

    if (session) {
      res.status(200).json({ message: 'User is authenticated', user: session.user });
    } else {
      res.status(401).json({ message: 'User is not authenticated' });
    }
  }
  ```
